<paragraph id="8475EC5DA23B1B2182DA4931FE065438" blockId="2.[151,1437,1657,1828]" pageId="2" pageNumber="117">
<emphasis id="B6BE304FA23B1B2182DA4931FE8D558F" bold="true" box="[151,378,1657,1684]" pageId="2" pageNumber="117">Updated diagnosis.</emphasis>
In addition to the diagnosis given by 
<bibRefCitation id="E05B91ACA23B1B2181524931FB705588" author="Bustamante, A. A. &amp; Ruiz, G. R. S." box="[799,1159,1658,1684]" pageId="2" pageNumber="117" pagination="301 - 347" refId="ref11153" refString="Bustamante, A. A. &amp; Ruiz, G. R. S. (2017) Systematics of Thiodinini (Araneae: Salticidae: Salticinae), with description of a new genus and twelve new species. Zootaxa, 4362 (3), 301 - 347. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4362.3.1" type="journal article" year="2017">Bustamante &amp; Ruiz (2017: 310)</bibRefCitation>
, we included the following comparisons due the description of 
<taxonomicName id="43CA97DEA23B1B21801749D5FCB455A4" authority="Bustamante &amp; Ruiz, 2020" authorityName="Bustamante &amp; Ruiz" authorityYear="2020" box="[602,835,1694,1720]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Cyllodania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="2" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marietae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B6BE304FA23B1B21801749D5FCB455A4" box="[602,835,1694,1720]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="117">Cyllodania marietae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B6BE304FA23B1B21810649D5FC5155A4" bold="true" box="[843,934,1694,1720]" pageId="2" pageNumber="117">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="AD8D8D34A23B1B21810649D5FC5155A4" box="[843,934,1694,1720]" pageId="2" pageNumber="117" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(see below): 
<taxonomicName id="43CA97DEA23B1B21860F49D5FB4955A4" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1902" box="[1090,1214,1694,1720]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Cyllodania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="2" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B6BE304FA23B1B21860F49D5FB4955A4" box="[1090,1214,1694,1720]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="117">Cyllodania</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles 
<taxonomicName id="43CA97DEA23B1B21877249D5FF1455C0" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1902" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Atomosphyrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="2" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B6BE304FA23B1B21877249D5FF1455C0" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="117">Atomosphyrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having a mastidion on male chelicera (common in amycoids), but differs by the presence of a distal projection on the embolus in the male palp and by having a longitudinal band of white scales on the abdomen dorsum and by having a wider femur I.
</paragraph>
